<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>{{ result.title }} — Debate Analysis</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Syne:wght@400;600;700;800&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --bg: #080a0f;
    --panel: rgba(5, 8, 15, 0.88);
    --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    --text: #e2e8f0;
    --text-dim: #94a3b8;
    --blue: #3b82f6;
    --orange: #f97316;
    --green: #22c55e;
    --yellow: #eab308;
    --red: #ef4444;
    --purple: #a855f7;
  }
  body {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    min-height: 100vh;
    position: relative;
  }
  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    opacity: 0.03;
    background: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 256 256' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cfilter id='n'%3E%3CfeTurbulence type='fractalNoise' baseFrequency='0.9' numOctaves='4' stitchTiles='stitch'/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' filter='url(%23n)'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  /* Nav */
  .nav { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; background: rgba(8,10,15,0.95); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 0; }
  .nav .container { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .nav-brand { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 800; font-size: 14px; letter-spacing: 3px; color: var(--text); }
  .nav-meta { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); }

  /* Hero */
  .hero { padding: 64px 0 48px; text-align: center; }
  .hero-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 2px; color: var(--text-dim); text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 36px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .hero-topic { font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .hero-meta { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .hero-meta span { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }

  /* Score Cards */
  .score-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .score-card { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 32px; }
  .score-card-name { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .score-card-number { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 72px; font-weight: 800; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .mini-bar-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .mini-bar-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); width: 120px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .mini-bar-track { flex: 1; height: 6px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden; }
  .mini-bar-fill { height: 100%; border-radius: 3px; transition: width 0.3s; }
  .mini-bar-value { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); width: 48px; text-align: right; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .score-card-footer { margin-top: 16px; padding-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); }

  /* Timeline */
  .timeline-section { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .section-title { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .timeline-track { position: relative; height: 32px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-radius: 4px; display: flex; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .timeline-segment { height: 100%; min-width: 1px; }
  .timeline-flags { position: relative; height: 20px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .flag-dot { position: absolute; width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; top: 6px; transform: translateX(-4px); cursor: pointer; }
  .flag-dot.dodge { background: var(--red); }
  .flag-dot.low_engagement { background: var(--yellow); }
  .flag-dot.topic_drift { background: var(--purple); }
  .flag-dot.correction { background: var(--orange); }
  .flag-dot.position_shift { background: #38bdf8; }
  .flag-dot.low_evidence { background: var(--text-dim); }
  .flag-dot .flag-tooltip { display: none; position: absolute; bottom: 18px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); background: rgba(0,0,0,0.92); color: var(--text); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 6px; white-space: nowrap; max-width: 400px; white-space: normal; z-index: 10; pointer-events: none; }
  .flag-dot:hover .flag-tooltip { display: block; }
  .timeline-axis { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .timeline-legend { display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-top: 12px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .legend-dot { display: inline-block; width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; margin-right: 4px; vertical-align: middle; }

  /* Stats Table */
  .stats-section { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; }
  th, td { padding: 14px 20px; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  th { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  td { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 14px; }
  td.metric-label { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-dim); }
  td.better { color: var(--green); font-weight: 700; }

  /* Flag Log */
  .flag-log-section { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .flag-entry { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px 20px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .flag-entry-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .flag-timestamp { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .flag-speaker { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; }
  .flag-badge { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; }
  .flag-badge.dodge { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.15); color: var(--red); }
  .flag-badge.low_engagement { background: rgba(234,179,8,0.15); color: var(--yellow); }
  .flag-badge.topic_drift { background: rgba(168,85,247,0.15); color: var(--purple); }
  .flag-badge.correction { background: rgba(249,115,22,0.15); color: var(--orange); }
  .flag-badge.position_shift { background: rgba(56,189,248,0.15); color: #38bdf8; }
  .flag-badge.low_evidence { background: rgba(148,163,184,0.15); color: var(--text-dim); }
  .flag-badge.ad_hominem { background: rgba(239,68,68,0.2); color: #f87171; }
  .flag-badge.strawman { background: rgba(251,146,60,0.15); color: #fb923c; }
  .flag-badge.whataboutism { background: rgba(234,179,8,0.2); color: #facc15; }
  .flag-badge.red_herring { background: rgba(168,85,247,0.2); color: #c084fc; }
  .flag-badge.gish_gallop { background: rgba(236,72,153,0.15); color: #f472b6; }
  .flag-badge.circular_reasoning { background: rgba(20,184,166,0.15); color: #2dd4bf; }
  .flag-badge.false_dichotomy { background: rgba(99,102,241,0.15); color: #818cf8; }
  .flag-dot.ad_hominem { background: #f87171; }
  .flag-dot.strawman { background: #fb923c; }
  .flag-dot.whataboutism { background: #facc15; }
  .flag-dot.red_herring { background: #c084fc; }
  .flag-dot.gish_gallop { background: #f472b6; }
  .flag-dot.circular_reasoning { background: #2dd4bf; }
  .flag-dot.false_dichotomy { background: #818cf8; }
  .fallacy-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .fallacy-card { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; }
  .fallacy-card-title { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .fallacy-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; }
  .fallacy-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .fallacy-name { color: var(--text-dim); text-transform: capitalize; }
  .fallacy-count { font-weight: 700; }
  .fallacy-count.zero { color: var(--green); }
  .fallacy-count.nonzero { color: var(--red); }
  .flag-quote { font-style: italic; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .flag-explanation { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-dim); }

  /* Methodology */
  .methodology { margin-bottom: 64px; }
  .methodology p { margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-dim); line-height: 1.7; }
  .methodology strong { color: var(--text); }
  .methodology pre { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-dim); overflow-x: auto; margin: 16px 0; }
  .methodology .disclaimer { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-dim); padding-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- Nav -->
<nav class="nav">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="nav-brand">DEBATESTATS</div>
    <div class="nav-meta">v0.1.0 — process metrics only — no opinion judgments</div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-label">Debate Analysis Report</div>
    <h1 class="hero-title">{{ result.title }}</h1>
    <p class="hero-topic">{{ result.topic }}</p>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span>{{ result.generated_at[:10] }}</span>
      <span>{{ result.duration_ms | ms_to_human }}</span>
      <span>{{ turns | length }} turns</span>
      <span>{{ flags | length }} flags</span>
      <span><a href="{{ result.youtube_url }}" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">YouTube ↗</a></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Score Cards -->
<section class="container">
  <div class="score-cards">
    {% for speaker in speakers %}
    {% if speaker in stats %}
    {% set s = stats[speaker] %}
    {% set color = '#3b82f6' if loop.index0 == 0 else '#f97316' %}
    <div class="score-card" style="border-top: 3px solid {{ color }};">
      <div class="score-card-name" style="color: {{ color }};">{{ speaker }}</div>
      <div class="score-card-number" style="color: {{ s.overall_score | score_color }};">{{ s.overall_score }}</div>

      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Claim Support</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ (s.claim_support_ratio * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format(s.claim_support_ratio * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Eng. Quality</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ (s.avg_engagement_quality * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format(s.avg_engagement_quality * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Fallacy-Free</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ ((1 - s.fallacy_rate) * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format((1 - s.fallacy_rate) * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Targeting</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ (s.avg_targeting_score * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format(s.avg_targeting_score * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Schemes</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ (s.scheme_diversity * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format(s.scheme_diversity * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mini-bar-row">
        <span class="mini-bar-label">Dodge Rate</span>
        <div class="mini-bar-track"><div class="mini-bar-fill" style="width: {{ ((1 - s.dodge_rate) * 100) | round(0) }}%; background: {{ color }};"></div></div>
        <span class="mini-bar-value">{{ '%.0f' | format(s.dodge_rate * 100) }}%</span>
      </div>

      <div class="score-card-footer">
        {{ flag_counts.get(speaker, 0) }} flags raised
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Timeline -->
<section class="container timeline-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Turn Timeline</h2>
  <div class="timeline-track">
    {% for turn in turns %}
    {% set width = ((turn.end_ms - turn.start_ms) / result.duration_ms * 100) %}
    {% set bg = 'rgba(59,130,246,0.5)' if turn.speaker == speakers[0] else 'rgba(249,115,22,0.5)' %}
    <div class="timeline-segment" style="width: {{ width }}%; background: {{ bg }};"></div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-flags">
    {% for flag in flags %}
    {% set left = (turns_by_index[flag.turn_index].start_ms / result.duration_ms * 100) %}
    <div class="flag-dot {{ flag.flag_type }}" style="left: {{ left }}%;">
      <div class="flag-tooltip">{{ flag.explanation }}</div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-axis">
    {% for i in range(5) %}
    <span>{{ (result.duration_ms * i / 4) | int | ms_to_timestamp }}</span>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <div class="timeline-legend" style="flex-wrap: wrap;">
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--red);"></span>Dodge</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--yellow);"></span>Low Engagement</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--purple);"></span>Topic Drift</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--orange);"></span>Correction</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #38bdf8;"></span>Position Shift</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: var(--text-dim);"></span>Low Evidence</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #f87171;"></span>Ad Hominem</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #fb923c;"></span>Strawman</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #facc15;"></span>Whataboutism</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #c084fc;"></span>Red Herring</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #f472b6;"></span>Gish Gallop</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #2dd4bf;"></span>Circular Reasoning</span>
    <span><span class="legend-dot" style="background: #818cf8;"></span>False Dichotomy</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Stats Table -->
<section class="container stats-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Detailed Comparison</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Metric</th>
        {% for speaker in speakers %}
        {% if speaker in stats %}
        <th style="color: {{ '#3b82f6' if loop.index0 == 0 else '#f97316' }};">{{ speaker }}</th>
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% set scored_speakers = [] %}
      {% for sp in speakers if sp in stats %}{% if scored_speakers.append(sp) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}

      {% if scored_speakers | length == 2 %}
      {% set sa = stats[scored_speakers[0]] %}
      {% set sb = stats[scored_speakers[1]] %}

      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Overall Score</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.overall_score >= sb.overall_score else '' }}">{{ sa.overall_score }}</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.overall_score >= sa.overall_score else '' }}">{{ sb.overall_score }}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Avg Engagement</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_engagement >= sb.avg_engagement else '' }}">{{ sa.avg_engagement }}</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_engagement >= sa.avg_engagement else '' }}">{{ sb.avg_engagement }}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Dodge Rate</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.dodge_rate <= sb.dodge_rate else '' }}">{{ sa.total_dodges }}/{{ sa.questions_faced }} ({{ (sa.dodge_rate * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.dodge_rate <= sa.dodge_rate else '' }}">{{ sb.total_dodges }}/{{ sb.questions_faced }} ({{ (sb.dodge_rate * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Claim Support Ratio</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.claim_support_ratio >= sb.claim_support_ratio else '' }}">{{ sa.supported_claims }}/{{ sa.total_claims }} ({{ (sa.claim_support_ratio * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.claim_support_ratio >= sa.claim_support_ratio else '' }}">{{ sb.supported_claims }}/{{ sb.total_claims }} ({{ (sb.claim_support_ratio * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Avg Topic Drift</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_topic_drift <= sb.avg_topic_drift else '' }}">{{ sa.avg_topic_drift }}</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_topic_drift <= sa.avg_topic_drift else '' }}">{{ sb.avg_topic_drift }}</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Correction Absorption<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">% of corrections acknowledged</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.correction_absorption_rate >= sb.correction_absorption_rate else '' }}">{{ sa.corrections_acknowledged }}/{{ sa.corrections_received }} ({{ (sa.correction_absorption_rate * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.correction_absorption_rate >= sa.correction_absorption_rate else '' }}">{{ sb.corrections_acknowledged }}/{{ sb.corrections_received }} ({{ (sb.correction_absorption_rate * 100) | round(0) | int }}%)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Position Consistency<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">EXPERIMENTAL — high shift counts expected in long debates</small></td>
        <td>{{ sa.consistency_score }} ({{ sa.position_shifts }} shifts)</td>
        <td>{{ sb.consistency_score }} ({{ sb.position_shifts }} shifts)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Concession Rate<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">willingness to concede valid points</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.concession_rate >= sb.concession_rate else '' }}">{{ sa.concessions_made }} ({{ (sa.concession_rate * 100) | round(1) }}%)</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.concession_rate >= sa.concession_rate else '' }}">{{ sb.concessions_made }} ({{ (sb.concession_rate * 100) | round(1) }}%)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Evidence Density<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">avg per turn (scored) · total markers (info only)</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_evidence_density >= sb.avg_evidence_density else '' }}">{{ sa.avg_evidence_density }} avg · {{ sa.total_evidence_markers }} total</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_evidence_density >= sa.avg_evidence_density else '' }}">{{ sb.avg_evidence_density }} avg · {{ sb.total_evidence_markers }} total</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Fallacy Rate<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">lower = cleaner argumentation</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.fallacy_rate <= sb.fallacy_rate else '' }}">{{ (sa.fallacy_rate * 100) | round(1) }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.fallacy_rate <= sa.fallacy_rate else '' }}">{{ (sb.fallacy_rate * 100) | round(1) }}%</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Engagement Quality<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">DQI 0-3 normalized</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_engagement_quality >= sb.avg_engagement_quality else '' }}">{{ (sa.avg_engagement_quality * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_engagement_quality >= sa.avg_engagement_quality else '' }}">{{ (sb.avg_engagement_quality * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Scheme Diversity<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">variety of argumentation schemes</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.scheme_diversity >= sb.scheme_diversity else '' }}">{{ (sa.scheme_diversity * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.scheme_diversity >= sa.scheme_diversity else '' }}">{{ (sb.scheme_diversity * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Targeting Score<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">targets opponent's strongest points</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_targeting_score >= sb.avg_targeting_score else '' }}">{{ (sa.avg_targeting_score * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_targeting_score >= sa.avg_targeting_score else '' }}">{{ (sb.avg_targeting_score * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Opponent Term Adoption<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">engagement with opponent's key terms</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_opponent_term_adoption >= sb.avg_opponent_term_adoption else '' }}">{{ (sa.avg_opponent_term_adoption * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_opponent_term_adoption >= sa.avg_opponent_term_adoption else '' }}">{{ (sb.avg_opponent_term_adoption * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Paraphrase Fidelity<br><small style="color:var(--text-dim);font-size:11px;">accuracy when restating opponent</small></td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sa.avg_paraphrase_fidelity >= sb.avg_paraphrase_fidelity else '' }}">{{ (sa.avg_paraphrase_fidelity * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if sb.avg_paraphrase_fidelity >= sa.avg_paraphrase_fidelity else '' }}">{{ (sb.avg_paraphrase_fidelity * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</td>
      </tr>
      {% set fc_a = flag_counts.get(scored_speakers[0], 0) %}
      {% set fc_b = flag_counts.get(scored_speakers[1], 0) %}
      <tr>
        <td class="metric-label">Total Flags</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if fc_a <= fc_b else '' }}">{{ fc_a }}</td>
        <td class="{{ 'better' if fc_b <= fc_a else '' }}">{{ fc_b }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endif %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<!-- Fallacy Breakdown -->
{% if scored_speakers | length == 2 %}
{% set sa = stats[scored_speakers[0]] %}
{% set sb = stats[scored_speakers[1]] %}
<section class="container" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
  <h2 class="section-title">Fallacy Breakdown</h2>
  <div class="fallacy-grid">
    {% for sp_idx in range(2) %}
    {% set s = sa if sp_idx == 0 else sb %}
    {% set color = '#3b82f6' if sp_idx == 0 else '#f97316' %}
    <div class="fallacy-card" style="border-top: 3px solid {{ color }};">
      <div class="fallacy-card-title" style="color: {{ color }};">{{ scored_speakers[sp_idx] }}</div>
      {% for ftype in ['ad_hominem', 'strawman', 'whataboutism', 'red_herring', 'gish_gallop', 'circular_reasoning', 'false_dichotomy'] %}
      {% set cnt = s.fallacy_counts.get(ftype, 0) %}
      <div class="fallacy-row">
        <span class="fallacy-name">{{ ftype | replace('_', ' ') }}</span>
        <span class="fallacy-count {{ 'zero' if cnt == 0 else 'nonzero' }}">{{ cnt }}</span>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
      <div class="fallacy-row" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 4px; padding-top: 8px; font-weight: 700;">
        <span class="fallacy-name" style="color: var(--text);">Total</span>
        {% set total = s.fallacy_counts.values() | sum %}
        <span class="fallacy-count {{ 'zero' if total == 0 else 'nonzero' }}">{{ total }}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Engagement Quality Distribution -->
<section class="container" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
  <h2 class="section-title">Engagement Quality Distribution</h2>
  <div class="fallacy-grid">
    {% for sp_idx in range(2) %}
    {% set sp = scored_speakers[sp_idx] %}
    {% set color = '#3b82f6' if sp_idx == 0 else '#f97316' %}
    {% set sp_turns = [] %}
    {% for t in turns if t.speaker == sp %}{% if sp_turns.append(t) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}
    <div class="fallacy-card" style="border-top: 3px solid {{ color }};">
      <div class="fallacy-card-title" style="color: {{ color }};">{{ sp }}</div>
      {% set level_labels = {0: 'No Engagement', 1: 'Negative Only', 2: 'Basic Engagement', 3: 'Quality Engagement'} %}
      {% set level_colors = {0: 'var(--red)', 1: 'var(--yellow)', 2: 'var(--text-dim)', 3: 'var(--green)'} %}
      {% for lvl in range(4) %}
      {% set cnt = sp_turns | selectattr('engagement_quality_level', 'equalto', lvl) | list | length %}
      <div class="fallacy-row">
        <span class="fallacy-name">Level {{ lvl }}: {{ level_labels[lvl] }}</span>
        <span class="fallacy-count" style="color: {{ level_colors[lvl] }};">{{ cnt }}</span>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Argumentation Schemes -->
<section class="container" style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
  <h2 class="section-title">Argumentation Schemes</h2>
  <div class="fallacy-grid">
    {% for sp_idx in range(2) %}
    {% set sp = scored_speakers[sp_idx] %}
    {% set color = '#3b82f6' if sp_idx == 0 else '#f97316' %}
    {% set sp_turns = [] %}
    {% for t in turns if t.speaker == sp %}{% if sp_turns.append(t) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}
    <div class="fallacy-card" style="border-top: 3px solid {{ color }};">
      <div class="fallacy-card-title" style="color: {{ color }};">{{ sp }}</div>
      {% set scheme_names = ['analogy', 'cause_effect', 'authority', 'example', 'sign', 'practical_reasoning', 'values'] %}
      {% for scheme in scheme_names %}
      {% set cnt = [] %}
      {% for t in sp_turns %}{% for s in t.schemes if s == scheme %}{% if cnt.append(1) %}{% endif %}{% endfor %}{% endfor %}
      <div class="fallacy-row">
        <span class="fallacy-name">{{ scheme | replace('_', ' ') }}</span>
        <span class="fallacy-count" style="color: {{ 'var(--green)' if cnt | length > 0 else 'var(--text-dim)' }};">{{ cnt | length }}</span>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
      {% set s_stat = sa if sp_idx == 0 else sb %}
      <div class="fallacy-row" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 4px; padding-top: 8px;">
        <span class="fallacy-name" style="color: var(--text); font-weight: 700;">Diversity</span>
        <span class="fallacy-count" style="color: var(--text); font-weight: 700;">{{ (s_stat.scheme_diversity * 100) | round(0) | int }}%</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<!-- Flag Log -->
<section class="container flag-log-section">
  <h2 class="section-title">Flag Log ({{ flags | length }} events)</h2>
  {% for g in grouped_flags %}
  {% set flag = g.flag %}
  {% set turn = turns_by_index[flag.turn_index] %}
  {% set color = '#3b82f6' if turn.speaker == speakers[0] else '#f97316' %}
  <div class="flag-entry">
    <div class="flag-entry-header">
      <span class="flag-timestamp">{{ turn.start_ms | ms_to_timestamp }}</span>
      <span class="flag-speaker" style="color: {{ color }};">{{ turn.speaker }}</span>
      <span class="flag-badge {{ flag.flag_type }}">{{ flag.flag_type | replace('_', ' ') }}{% if g.count > 1 %} &times;{{ g.count }}{% endif %}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="flag-quote">"{{ turn.text[:120] }}{% if turn.text | length > 120 %}...{% endif %}"</div>
    <div class="flag-explanation">{{ flag.explanation }}{% if g.extra > 0 %} +{{ g.extra }} more questions flagged in this turn{% endif %}</div>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<!-- Methodology -->
<section class="container methodology">
  <h2 class="section-title">Methodology</h2>

  <p><strong>Engagement Score:</strong> Cosine similarity between the speaker's response and the opponent's previous turn. Measures how directly someone addresses what was just said.</p>

  <p><strong>Question Dodge Rate:</strong> When a turn contains a direct question, the responder's next turn is compared semantically. Below-threshold similarity is flagged as a dodge.</p>

  <p><strong>Claim Support Ratio:</strong> Declarative sentences are classified as supported (containing reasoning connectors like 'because', 'therefore', 'evidence shows') or unsupported. Ratio of supported to total.</p>

  <p><strong>Topic Drift Index:</strong> Each turn is compared semantically to the agreed debate topic. High distance means the speaker is steering conversation elsewhere.</p>

  <p><strong>Correction Absorption:</strong> When speaker A corrects speaker B, we check whether B's next turn acknowledges the correction (cosine similarity ≥ 0.20). Higher absorption = better.</p>

  <p><strong>Position Consistency:</strong> Each speaker's later turns are compared to their own earlier turns. Very low similarity flags a potential position shift. Higher score = more consistent.</p>

  <p><strong>Concession Rate:</strong> Counts explicit concession phrases ("fair point", "you're right", etc.). Higher = more intellectually honest.</p>

  <p><strong>Evidence Density:</strong> Counts concrete evidence markers per turn — years, percentages, named sources, statistics, direct quotes. Higher = more evidence-backed.</p>

  <p><strong>Fallacy Detection:</strong> Identifies 7 logical fallacy patterns: ad hominem, strawman, whataboutism, red herring, Gish Gallop, circular reasoning, and false dichotomy. Combines regex patterns with semantic analysis.</p>

  <p><strong>Engagement Quality:</strong> Classifies turns into DQI levels 0-3 based on cosine similarity, concession markers, and rebuttal indicators. Level 3 = quality engagement with substance.</p>

  <p><strong>Argumentation Schemes:</strong> Detects 7 argument types (analogy, cause/effect, authority, example, sign, practical reasoning, values). Scheme diversity measures range across a speaker's turns.</p>

  <p><strong>Targeting Score:</strong> Measures whether rebuttals address the opponent's strongest points (sentences with evidence, named entities, reasoning connectors) rather than weaker arguments.</p>

  <pre>score = (claim_support_ratio × 15)
      + (engagement_quality × 12)
      + (correction_absorption × 12)
      + ((1 − fallacy_rate) × 12)
      + (targeting_score × 8)
      + (paraphrase_fidelity × 8)
      + (opponent_term_adoption × 8)
      + (evidence_density × 100 × 8)
      + ((1 − dodge_rate) × 7)
      + (scheme_diversity × 5)
      + ((1 − avg_topic_drift) × 3)
      + (concession_rate × 100 × 2)</pre>

  <p class="disclaimer">No LLM judges the content or opinions expressed. All metrics are mathematical. Source code is open.</p>
</section>

</body>
</html>
